50|$|The lesser sac, {{also known}} as the omental bursa, is the cavity in the abdomen that is formed by the <b>lesser</b> and greater <b>omentum.</b> Usually found in mammals, it is {{connected}} with the greater sac via the omental foramen (previously known as the Foramen of Winslow). In mammals, {{it is not uncommon for}} the lesser sac to contain considerable amounts of fat.|$|R
